---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---
<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy - Aegis"
  description="Aegis Privacy Policy. Aegis does not collect, store, or process personal data."
  canonicalUrl="https://aegis-defi.netlify.app/privacy"
>
  <header class="w-full py-6 px-8 border-b border-outline-variant/20">
    <div class="max-w-screen-md mx-auto flex items-center gap-3">
      <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-2">
        <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
          <path d="M12 2L3 7v5c0 5.55 3.84 10.74 9 12 5.16-1.26 9-6.45 9-12V7l-9-5z" fill="#070d1f" stroke="#ffe792" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <path d="M9 12l2 2 4-4" stroke="#ffe792" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
        </svg>
        <span class="text-lg font-bold text-on-surface font-headline">Aegis</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="max-w-screen-md mx-auto px-8 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold font-headline text-primary mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-on-surface-variant text-sm mb-12">Last updated: March 21, 2026</p>

    <div class="space-y-10 text-on-surface/90 leading-relaxed">

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold font-headline text-on-surface mb-3">The short version</h2>
        <p>Aegis does not collect your data. It runs on your machine. We do not track you, profile you, or sell anything about you to anyone.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold font-headline text-on-surface mb-3">How Aegis works</h2>
        <p>Aegis is an MCP server that runs locally on your computer. All contract analysis, transaction simulation, and risk scoring happens on your machine or through direct RPC calls to public blockchain nodes. Your data stays with you.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold font-headline text-on-surface mb-3">What we do not collect</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mt-2 text-on-surface-variant">
          <li>No personally identifiable information (PII)</li>
          <li>No wallet addresses, private keys, or seed phrases</li>
          <li>No transaction history or trading activity</li>
          <li>No usage analytics or telemetry</li>
          <li>No IP addresses or device fingerprints</li>
          <li>No cookies, tracking pixels, or third-party scripts</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold font-headline text-on-surface mb-3">The landing page</h2>
        <p>This website (aegis-defi.netlify.app) is a static page hosted on Netlify. It does not use cookies, analytics, or tracking scripts of any kind. Netlify may collect standard server logs (IP address, request time, page visited) as part of their hosting infrastructure. See <a href="https://www.netlify.com/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-primary hover:underline">Netlify's privacy policy</a> for details on their data practices.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold font-headline text-on-surface mb-3">On-chain transactions</h2>
        <p>If you use Aegis on-chain contracts on Base, your transactions are recorded on a public blockchain. This is how blockchains work. Transaction data, wallet addresses, and contract interactions are publicly visible to anyone. This is not something Aegis controls or can change.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold font-headline text-on-surface mb-3">Third-party RPC providers</h2>
        <p>Aegis makes RPC calls to blockchain nodes to fetch contract data and simulate transactions. If you use a third-party RPC provider (such as Alchemy, Infura, or QuickNode), that provider may collect data according to their own privacy policy. You can configure Aegis to use any RPC endpoint, including your own node.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold font-headline text-on-surface mb-3">Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>If we ever change this policy, we will update this page. Given that Aegis does not collect data, we do not expect significant changes.</p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>

  <footer class="bg-surface-container-lowest w-full py-12 border-t border-outline-variant/20">
    <div class="max-w-screen-md mx-auto px-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-4">
      <p class="text-outline text-sm">Aegis. MIT License.</p>
      <div class="flex gap-6">
        <a class="text-outline hover:text-on-surface transition-colors text-sm" href="/">Home</a>
        <a class="text-outline hover:text-on-surface transition-colors text-sm" href="/terms">Terms</a>
        <a class="text-outline hover:text-on-surface transition-colors text-sm" href="https://github.com/StanleytheGoat/aegis" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Layout>
